description: Immunometabolism at maternal-fetal interface: interactions between the hormones progesterone (P4), estrogen (estradiol, E2), and human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG) and uterine nk cells (uNK). This model represents the secretory phase of the menstrual cycle and first trimester period of pregnancy for these interactions.
title: Interactions between uterine natural killer cells and progesterone, estrogen, and human chorionic gonadotropin.
